{
  "text": "Lastly, and in full accordance with our results, Cha and co-workers detected by IHC significantly induced caspase-cleaved cytokeratin-18 (cCK-18) in AECIIs of IPF patients in comparison to normal lungs. Cell lysates of isolated AECIIs from patients with IPF revealed increased XBP1-splicing and concomitantly elevated levels of activated, phosphorylated IRE1\u03b1 (p-IRE1\u03b1) [CITATION_1] , which has been reported to induce directly various pro-apoptotic pathways independent of those activated by XBP1 [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . In full agreement with this notion, incubation of A549 cells with thapsigargin resulted in increased IRE1\u03b1-phosphorylation and formation of cCK-18 [CITATION_7] .",
  "correct_citation": {
